hey kids 

for the last little while I’ve been puttin the finishing touches on my new record

it’s coming your way 🔜, so I thought i’d tell you about it about it in advance. 

I know ; a novel concept. Anyway, it’s called Someday it Won’t Feel Like Dying. A Heartbreak album she be 🏴‍☠️, about getting yourself back to zero, or, y’know, to feeling like a whole person, even though it’s just you again : your best buddy’s gone for good. Thanks to my friends, and the many wonderful artists I get to collaborate with, I did.
my first single in a while, ‘Beyond The Pale,’ coming June 23rd, w music vid shot in Poland by @office_party  xoxox

“Beyond the Pale”🐺 first single & vid off Someday it Won’t Feel Like Dying out 6/23

I originally wanted to call it “ “ but was advised against it. Swipe left for a sneak peek 👀 at the ideas factory 🏭

For NYC friends, please join me for the in-person reception at the Roxy Hotel 6/22. Limited spots available! To secure a spot for you and 1 guest, fill out the RSVP form- link in my bio.

i think of myself as the star in my own confusing multiverse movie 👥

“Beyond The Pale” single and video out at midnight 6/23 on Think Think Think records

vid premiere @ Roxy Hotel 6/22. RSVP link in bio- limited spots available. Hope to see y’all jumping for joy like Jamie Lee. Be there or be a square in every universe 🌌

I think the greatest thing about working in film our first time was the wonderfully large array of people involved & the humanity in these dreamers, these people who wanted to make their contribution to making art in whatever way.  It tends to bring out the best people, and the best in people. And that humanity and aspiration had an effect on us and made us want to honor the sacrifice of time and life force that everyone was making by pushing ourselves to try to make some magic, and the best magic we could possibly make. 
So it comes as a humbling moment when your labor is recognized by your peers after the fact, in whatever way. 
Much love to all our fellow laborers in this struggle to solve problems and make a bit of magic 🪄 ❤️ @iammarkronson @abbeyroadstudios
